<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.1202993>
    dc:description "FIGURE 20. Caligus biseriodentatus Shen, 1957, female. A, habitus, dorsal; B, sternal furca; C, distal exopodal segment of leg 1; D, endopod of leg 2; E, modified plumose seta from third segment of exopod of leg 2; F, exopod of leg 4. Male, G, habitus, dorsal; H, maxilliped; I, distal exopodal segment of leg 1; J, exopod of leg 4. Scale bars: 1.0 mm on A, G, 200 µm on H, 100 µm on C, D, J, 50 µm on B, E, F, I." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/1202993/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

